{{Infobox meteorite |Name= Avanhandava |Type= Chondrite |Class= [[Ordinary chondrite]] |Group=H4 |Structural_classification= |Composition= |Shock= |Weathering= |Country= [[Brazil]] |Region= [[Sao Paulo]] |Lat_Long= {{coord|21|27|37|S|49|57|3|W|display=inline,title}}<ref name=metbull>{{metbull|4905|Avanhandava}}</ref> |Observed_fall= Yes |Fall_date=1952 |Found_date= |TKW= 9.33 kg |Image2= |Image2_caption= }} '''Avanhandava''' is an [[H chondrite]] [[meteorite]] that fell to earth in 1952 in [[São Paulo]], [[Brazil]].<ref>[http://www.lpi.usra.edu/meetings/metsoc2005/pdf/download/alpha_j-l.pdf 68th Annual Meteoritical Society Meeting (2005) , Chondrule Magnetic Conglomerate Test of Avanhandava H4 Chondrite (T. Kohout and L. J. Pesonen, p.5202]</ref>
A total of {{convert|9.33|kg}} of this meteorite was collected after it broke up during its impact with the Earth.<ref>[http://adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2005AGUFMGP43A0886K The Smithsonian/NASA Astrophysics Data System]</ref>
==Classification== It is classified as H4-[[ordinary chondrite]].<ref name=metbull />
