The '''Budd Kerr Baseball Museum''' is located in [[Vancouver, British Columbia]], [[Canada]] inside [[Nat Bailey Stadium]], the home of the [[Vancouver Canadiens]]. The museum, which opened on June 18, 2008, is dedicated to the more than sixty years of baseball that have been played in that stadium.<ref name="milb">{{cite news|last1=Fai|first1=Rob|title=Bud Kerr Museum brings back memories for fans both young and old|url=https://www.milb.com/canadians/news/bud-kerr-museum-brings-back-memories-for-fans-both-young-and-old/c-574846/t-196097408|accessdate=30 July 2017|publisher=Vancouver Canadians Baseball Club|date=2009-05-01}}</ref> The museum is named for Budd Kerr, the team's official historian until his death in 2009,<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hawthorn|first1=Tom|title=Ultimate baseball fan helped save Nat Bailey Stadium|url=http://v1.theglobeandmail.com/servlet/story/LAC.20090728.OBKERR28ART2037/BDAStory/BDA/deaths|accessdate=30 July 2017|work=Globe and Mail|date=2009-07-28}}</ref> and celebrates the players who have spent some of their careers there including: [[Rich Harden]], [[Sammy Sosa]], and [[Tim Raines]], who helped open the museum.<ref name="funf">{{cite web|last1=Scadden|first1=Natalie|title=Fun Facts from the Bud Kerr Baseball Museum|url=https://vancouverextrainnings.wordpress.com/2015/07/13/fun-facts-budd-kerr-museum519/|website=C's Extra Innings|accessdate=30 July 2017}}</ref><ref name="milb"/>

